         <abstract>
            <p>The stability of the $L_2$-projection onto some standard finite element spaces $V_h$, considered as a map in $L_p$ and $W{}_p^1, 1 \leqslant p \leqslant \infty$, is shown under weaker regularity requirements than quasi-uniformity of the triangulations underlying the definitions of the $V_h$.</p>
          </abstract>
